<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>At the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://forums.unrealengine.com/showthread.php?14834-Tutorial-Reflecting-Projectile-%28C-%29">suggestion</a> of Adam Davis, I have reproduced my website's reflecting projectile <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://theokrin.com/?p=126">tutorial</a> here.  This tutorial will cover setting up the project and detailing in depth what changes I made to produce the end result.  So read on to see how to make a reflecting projectile in Unreal Engine 4.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Assumptions">Assumptions</span></h2>
<p>First off, this tutorial is aimed at beginners, but you should be familiar with navigating the Editor and compiling Visual Studio projects.  Also, this project was created using version 4.2.1 of UE4, and it was compiled using Visual Studio 2013.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="The_Goal">The Goal</span></h2>
<p>I'll start by showing off a quick video that demonstrates the end goal of this tutorial.  The green lines are the initial path the projectile took, and when it is reflected the line changes to red.
</p><p><iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/qQxCxW98e_g" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> 
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Setting_Up_the_Project">Setting Up the Project</span></h2>
<p>First we want to launch the Editor via the Unreal Engine Launcher and create a new project.
</p>
<div class="thumb tnone"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:452px;"><a href="/File:Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/c/cb/Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png/450px-Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png" width="450" height="339" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/c/cb/Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png/675px-Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png 1.5x, https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/c/cb/Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png/900px-Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:Theokrin_TRP1_LaunchEditor.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>Launch UE4 4.2.1</div></div></div>
<p>Once the Editor's Project Browser is open.  Click the New Project tab at the top.  Choose Code First Person from the list as the project to create.  For reference, I named mine WPPost2.  Thus in screenshots/code samples my projectile class will be WPPost2Projectile.
</p>
<div class="thumb tnone"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:452px;"><a href="/File:Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/e/e7/Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png/450px-Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png" width="450" height="355" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/e/e7/Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png/675px-Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png 1.5x, https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/e/e7/Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png/900px-Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:Theokrin_TRP2_ProjectBrowser.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>Create project</div></div></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Remove_Existing_Projectile_Code">Remove Existing Projectile Code</span></h2>
<p>After you click Create Project, Visual Studio should open the project's solution automatically.  By default the project will come with a projectile class called &lt;ProjectName&gt;Projectile.h and &lt;ProjectName&gt;Projectile.cpp, and these files are found in the &lt;ProjectName&gt; folder under the Source folder in the project hierarchy.
</p>
<div class="thumb tnone"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:355px;"><a href="/File:Theokrin_TRP3_ProjectHiearchy.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://d26ilriwvtzlb.cloudfront.net/c/c7/Theokrin_TRP3_ProjectHiearchy.png" width="353" height="556" class="thumbimage" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:Theokrin_TRP3_ProjectHiearchy.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>Project hiearchy in Visual Studio</div></div></div>
<p>This class comes predefined with a UProjectileMovementComponent as a member component.  We want to remove this component and its associated code.  Because we will be adding our own logic in later.  I've highlighted the lines we'll be removing from the header and source files.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Before_-_WPPost2Projectile.h">Before - WPPost2Projectile.h</span></h3>
<div dir="ltr" class="mw-geshi mw-code mw-content-ltr"><div class="cpp source-cpp"><ol><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="co1">// Copyright 1998-2014 Epic Games, Inc. All Rights Reserved.</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="co2">#pragma once</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="co2">#include &quot;WPPost2Projectile.generated.h&quot;</span></pre></li><li class="li2"><pre class="de2">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">UCLASS<span class="br0">&#40;</span>config<span class="sy1">=</span>Game<span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="kw2">class</span> AWPPost2Projectile <span class="sy4">:</span> <span class="kw2">public</span> AActor</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="br0">&#123;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">    GENERATED_UCLASS_BODY<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></li><li class="li2"><pre class="de2">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">    <span class="coMULTI">/** Sphere collision component */</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">    UPROPERTY<span class="br0">&#40;</span>VisibleDefaultsOnly, Category<span class="sy1">=</span>Projectile<span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">    TSubobjectPtr<span class="sy1">&lt;</span>USphereComponent<span class="sy1">&gt;</span> CollisionComp<span class="sy4">;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li2 ln-xtra"><pre class="de2">    <span class="coMULTI">/** Projectile movement component */</span></pre></li><li class="li1 ln-xtra"><pre class="de1">    UPROPERTY<span class="br0">&#40;</span>VisibleAnywhere, BlueprintReadOnly, Category<span class="sy1">=</span>Movement<span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></li><li class="li1 ln-xtra"><pre class="de1">    TSubobjectPtr<span class="sy1">&lt;</span><span class="kw2">class</span> UProjectileMovementComponent<span class="sy1">&gt;</span> ProjectileMovement<span class="sy4">;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1 ln-xtra"><pre class="de1">    <span class="coMULTI">/** called when projectile hits something */</span></pre></li><li class="li2 ln-xtra"><pre class="de2">    UFUNCTION<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></li><li class="li1 ln-xtra"><pre class="de1">    <span class="kw4">void</span> OnHit<span class="br0">&#40;</span>AActor<span class="sy2">*</span> OtherActor, UPrimitiveComponent<span class="sy2">*</span> OtherComp, FVector NormalImpulse, <span class="kw4">const</span> FHitResult<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> Hit<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="br0">&#125;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre></li></ol></div></div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Before_-_WPPost2Projectile.cpp">Before - WPPost2Projectile.cpp</span></h3>
<div dir="ltr" class="mw-geshi mw-code mw-content-ltr"><div class="cpp source-cpp"><ol><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="co1">// Copyright 1998-2014 Epic Games, Inc. All Rights Reserved.</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="co2">#include &quot;WPPost2.h&quot;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="co2">#include &quot;WPPost2Projectile.h&quot;</span></pre></li><li class="li2"><pre class="de2">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">&#160;</pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">AWPPost2Projectile<span class="sy4">::</span><span class="me2">AWPPost2Projectile</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">const</span> <span class="kw2">class</span> FPostConstructInitializeProperties<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> PCIP<span class="br0">&#41;</span> </pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">	<span class="sy4">:</span> Super<span class="br0">&#40;</span>PCIP<span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1"><span class="br0">&#123;</span></pre></li><li class="li2"><pre class="de2">    <span class="co1">// Use a sphere as a simple collision representation</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">    CollisionComp <span class="sy1">=</span> PCIP.<span class="me1">CreateDefaultSubobject</span><span class="sy1">&lt;</span>USphereComponent<span class="sy1">&gt;</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw3">this</span>, TEXT<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="st0">&quot;SphereComp&quot;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre></li><li class="li1"><pre class="de1">    CollisionComp<span class="sy2">-</span><span class="sy1">&gt;</span>InitSphereRadius<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="nu17">5.0f</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre></li><li class="li1 ln-xtra"><pre class="de1">    CollisionComp<span class=